You can fill this out each time you are tested, and each time you receive a result. If you are sharing your information, having the result may be important when combined with your symptoms and other information.

The nasal swab test is used to show whether you currently are infected with the virus (antigen test) . The blood (antibody) test is used to show if you were previously infected. Neither test is completely accurate, and they measure different things.

Answer "positive" if your test shows that you have, or had, the virus. Answer "negative" if your test shows that you do/did not have the virus. You can also indicate if your test was inconclusive (which is uncommon), or if you are still awaiting the test result.

We’d like to know about conditions that may increase your COVID-19 risk. You can answer as many or as few of the following questions as you would like. If you do provide this information it may be useful for public health planning. This information will not be shared with anyone unless you have chosen to allow us to share your information.
